Name: nOfAllocatedInRep
Desc: Number of InReports which are currently allocated (i.e. which have been successfully created by the InFactory and not yet released)

Name: nOfAllocatedInCmd
Desc: Number of InCommands which are currently allocated (i.e. which have been successfully created by the InFactory and not yet released)

Name: nOfAllocatedOutCmp
Desc: Number of OutComponents which are currently allocated (i.e. which have been successfully created by the OutFactory and not yet released)

Name: nOfFailedInRep
Desc: Number of InReports whose creation by the InFactory failed

Name: nOfFailedInCmd
Desc: Number of InCommands whose creation by the InFactory failed

Name: nOfFailedOutCmp
Desc: Number of OutComponents whose creation by the OutFactory failed

Name: nOfTotAllocatedInRep
Desc: Number of InReports successfully created by the InFactory since application start

Name: nOfTotAllocatedInCmd
Desc: Number of InCommands successfully created by the InFactory since application start

Name: nOfTotAllocatedOutCmp
Desc: Number of OutComponents successfully created by the InFactory since application start

Name: nOfAccFailed
Desc: Number of commands which have failed their acceptance check since the application was last reset

Name: failCodeAccFailed
Desc: Failure code of last command which failed its Acceptance Check

Name: pcktIdAccFailed
Desc: Packet identifier of last command which failed its Acceptance Check

Name: nOfStartFailed
Desc: Number of commands which have failed their Start Check since the application was last reset

Name: failCodeStartFailed
Desc: Failure code of last command which failed its Start Check

Name: pcktIdStartFailed
Desc: Packet identifier of last command which failed its Start Check

Name: nOfPrgrFailed
Desc: Number of commands which have failed their Progress Check since the application was last reset

Name: failCodePrgrFailed
Desc: Failure code of last command which failed its Progress Check

Name: pcktIdPrgrFailed
Desc: Packet identifier of last command which failed its Progress Check

Name: stepPrgrFailed
Desc: Step identifier of last command which failed its Progress Check

Name: nOfTermFailed
Desc: Number of commands which have failed their Termination Check since the application was last reset

Name: failCodeTermFailed
Desc: Failure code of last command which failed its Termination Check

Name: pcktIdTermFailed
Desc: Packet identifier of last command which failed its Termination Check

Name: nOfReroutingFailed
Desc: Number of commands for which re-routing failed

Name: pcktIdReroutingFailed
Desc: Packet identifier of last command for which re-routing failed

Name: invDestRerouting
Desc: Destination of last command for which re-routing failed

Name: verFailData
Desc: Verification Failure Data (data item of fixed size but variable type with command-specific information about the last verification failure)

Name: cycleCnt
Desc: Array of HK\_N\_REP\_DEF elements. The i-th element is the cycle counter for the i-th Report Definitions in the RDL

Name: campleBufId
Desc: Array of HK\_N\_REP\_DEF elements. The i-th element is the identifier of the Sampling Buffer ter for the i-th Report Definition in the RDL

Name: isEnabled
Desc: Array of HK\_N\_REP\_DEF elements. The i-th element is the enable status of the i-th Report Definition in the RDL

Name: debugVar
Desc: Array of HK\_N\_DEBUG\_VAR elements. The i-th element is the value of the i-th debug variable

Name: nOfDisabledEid1
Desc: Number of event identifiers of level 1 which are disabled

Name: nOfDetectedEvts1
Desc: Number of detected occurrences of level 1 events

Name: nOfGenEvtRep1
Desc: Number of generated level 1 event reports

Name: lastEvtEid1
Desc: Event identifier of the last generated level 1 event report

Name: lastEvtTime1
Desc: Time when the last level 1 event report was generated

Name: isEidEnabled1
Desc: Array of EVT\_N\_EID1 elements holding the enable status of the level 1 event identifiers

Name: nOfDisabledEid2
Desc: Number of event identifiers of level 2 which are disabled

Name: nOfDetectedEvts2
Desc: Number of detected occurrences of level 2 events

Name: nOfGenEvtRep2
Desc: Number of generated level 2 event reports

Name: lastEvtEid2
Desc: Event identifier of the last generated level 2 event report

Name: lastEvtTime2
Desc: Time when the last level 2 event report was generated

Name: isEidEnabled2
Desc: Array of EVT\_N\_EID2 elements holding the enable status of the level 2 event identifiers

Name: nOfDisabledEid3
Desc: Number of event identifiers of level 3 which are disabled

Name: nOfDetectedEvts3
Desc: Number of detected occurrences of level 3 events

Name: nOfGenEvtRep3
Desc: Number of generated level 3 event reports

Name: lastEvtEid3
Desc: Event identifier of the last generated level 3 event report

Name: lastEvtTime3
Desc: Time when the last level 3 event report was generated

Name: isEidEnabled3
Desc: Array of EVT\_N\_EID3 elements holding the enable status of the level 3 event identifiers

Name: nOfDisabledEid4
Desc: Number of event identifiers of level 4 which are disabled

Name: nOfDetectedEvts4
Desc: Number of detected occurrences of level 4 events

Name: nOfGenEvtRep4
Desc: Number of generated level 4 event reports

Name: lastEvtEid4
Desc: Event identifier of the last generated level 4 event report

Desc: Time when the last level 4 event report was generated

Desc: Array of EVT\_N\_EID4 elements holding the enable status of the level 4 event identifiers

Name: areYouAliveSrc
Desc: Source of the latest (17,2) report received in response to a (17,1) command triggered by a (17,3) command
